My company has been using JIRA, Agile, and Fisheye for several years now.  We are currently evaluating Confluence 5.5.2.  So far, it has received extremely favorable reviews from our development and management teams.  One glaring missing feature, which apparently was available in previous versions of Confluence, is the ability to receive the full content of created/updated page in email notifications.  Many of our team members work a good part of their time outside of our internal network and will not be able to simply click a link on an email and reach our Confluence installation.  We need to see the entire page content in the email itself.  It looks as though the previously existing feature has been requested to be returned over and over again, as in CONF-28503.  

Well, here is another request to bring back this feature.  Or, can someone explain to me how I can enable this feature in Confluence 5.5.2?  My team wants the ability to simply click on the "Share" button and send an email to team members that includes the entire content of the page they are sharing, not just a link back to the page in Confluence.

