When users to attempt to copy external content from websites into Confluence, all the images are referenced instead of adding into Confluence.

If the external website is broken, the image will not be displayed since it is referenced. 

The current workaround for customer is to save external image to own machine, then manually add 1 by 1 into Confluence. Imagine if users have more than 10 images to copy on one article; it will take a lot of time just to insert image into Confluence.

